==English==

===Etymology===
A later {{inh|en|enm|-}} spelling, retaining the voiceless {{m|enm|-s}}, of {{m|enm|hennes}} ({{m|enm|henne}} + adverbial genitive ending {{m|enm|-s}}), from {{der|en|ang|heonan|t=away", "hence}}, from a {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*hin-}}. 

Cognate with {{cog|osx|hinan}}, {{cog|goh|hinnan}} ({{cog|de|hinnen}}), {{cog|nl|heen}}, {{cog|sv|hän}}. Related to Old English {{m|ang|her|t=here}}.

